### Initializing Rope Joint with react-three-rapier (TSX)

Source: https://github.com/pmndrs/react-three-rapier/blob/main/packages/react-three-rapier/readme.md

Demonstrates how to create a rope joint between two rigid bodies using useRopeJoint. It requires references to the two RigidBody instances and specifies the joint's local positions on each body and the maximum distance (rope length).

```tsx
const JointedThing = () => {
  const bodyA = useRef<RapierRigidBody>(null);
  const bodyB = useRef<RapierRigidBody>(null);

  const joint = useRopeJoint(bodyA, bodyB, [
    // Position of the joint in bodyA's local space
    [0, 0, 0],
    // Position of the joint in bodyB's local space
    [0, 0, 0],
    // The max distance between the two bodies / length of the rope
    1
  ]);

  return (
    <group>
      <RigidBody ref={bodyA}>
        <mesh />
      </RigidBody>
      <RigidBody ref={bodyB}>
        <mesh />
      </RigidBody>
    </group>
  );
};
```

