### Creating Revolute Joint in React Three Rapier (TSX)

Source: https://github.com/pmndrs/react-three-rapier/blob/main/packages/react-three-rapier/readme.md

Demonstrates how to use the useRevoluteJoint hook to create a hinge-like connection between two rigid bodies, allowing rotation along a specified axis. It requires refs to the rigid bodies and specifies the joint's position and axis in local space for both bodies.

```tsx
const JointedThing = () => {
  const bodyA = useRef<RapierRigidBody>(null);
  const bodyB = useRef<RapierRigidBody>(null);

  const joint = useRevoluteJoint(bodyA, bodyB, [
    // Position of the joint in bodyA's local space
    [0, 0, 0],
    // Position of the joint in bodyB's local space
    [0, 0, 0],
    // Axis of the joint, expressed in the local-space of
    // the rigid-bodies it is attached to. Cannot be [0,0,0].
    [0, 1, 0]
  ]);

  return (
    <group>
      <RigidBody ref={bodyA}>
        <mesh />
      </RigidBody>
      <RigidBody ref={bodyB}>
        <mesh />
      </RigidBody>
    </group>
  );
};
```

