### Configuring the Physics Component in React Three Rapier

Source: https://github.com/pmndrs/react-three-rapier/blob/main/readme.md

Shows how to configure the root <Physics /> component. It sets custom gravity, disables interpolation, and disables automatic colliders. The component must be wrapped in <Suspense /> as it lazily initializes the Rapier physics engine.

```tsx
const Scene = () => {
  return (
    <Canvas>
      <Suspense>
        <Physics gravity={[0, 1, 0]} interpolation={false} colliders={false}>
          ...
        </Physics>
      </Suspense>
    </Canvas>
  );
};
```

